text:
Lexington Ave., west side, north from East 67th to 68th Streets, showing the Institution for Deaf Mutes occupying this entire block front. This photograph taken after the "Great Blizzard" shows on the right, buildings at the N.W. corner of the avenue and 68th Street. These are units of the former Teachers (Normal) College and have been replaced by Thomas Hunter Hall (unit of Hunter College).

March 14, 1888.

Ewing Galloway.
